Salmonella & sugar gliders as pets: RFI 980508070407
[1
Date: Fri, 08 May 1998 08:11:47 -0400
From: Daniel S. Shapiro <dshapiro@bu.edu>

[1 There were 3 cases of salmonellosis in 1 family in one of the tables in
the paper:
David L. Woodward, Rasik Khakhria and Wendy M. Johnson. Human Salmonellosis
Associated with Exotic Pets, JCM, Vol. 35, No. 11, Nov. 1997, 2786 - 2790.
[2 For those who want to see a case report of another marsupial-associated
case of salmonellosis, please see:

Iveson JB, Bradshaw SD. Salmonella javiana infection in an infant
associated with a marsupial, the quokka, Setonix brachyurus, in Western
Australia. J Hyg (Lond) 1973 Sep;71(3):423-32.
If you are interested in zoonotic infections, please look at my web site
(which I do need to update) <http://medicine.bu.edu/dshapiro/zoo1.htm> and
give me feedback on diseases that I have not included (with a relevant
journal citation). Thank you.
